If Asian carp reach the Great Lakes it would devastate the $7 billion Great Lakes fishery and the 75,000+ jobs the fishery supports. I will continue to do everything in my power to prevent this from happening.

Proud to support the Frank LoBiondo Coast Guard Reauthorization Act, which establishes a Great Lakes Invasive Species Monitoring Program to better monitor the #GreatLakes ecosystem & prevent the spread of aquatic invasive species like Asian carp. pic.twitter.com/TXs15brRl9
